<br>
If your personal resists go over 100, then your pet will use your resists instead of its own.  If your personal resists stay under 100, then it will use its own resists. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hidroponnik>HidroPonnik</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#333333>(3/5/03 11:55:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1021.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Pets level of Resists</span><hr size=1> Thanks for the info..   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=limpylionbait>LimpyLionBait</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 301<br> <font color=#333333>(3/6/03 5:53:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1021.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Pets level of Resists</span><hr size=1> &gt; If your personal resists go over 100, then your pet will use your resists instead of its own. If your personal resists stay under 100, then it will use its own resists.<br>
